# u-forge.ai Project Structure Guide

Local-first TTRPG worldbuilding tool with AI-powered knowledge graphs.

Full workspace layout, SQLite schema, inference architecture, and design
decisions live in [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:ARCHITECTURE.md). Source files are
thoroughly commented — read them for file-level detail. This guide covers
cross-cutting integration rules that aren't obvious from any single file.

---

## Key Integration Points

### `EmbeddingProvider` is the only abstraction for embedding work

Lives in `crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/embeddings.rs`. `LemonadeProvider`
(`lemonade/embedding.rs`) is the only impl. **Do NOT bypass the trait** by
calling HTTP clients directly from business logic — the queue, search, and
ingest pipelines consume the trait object.

### `TranscriptionProvider` has two impls, picked by contention

- `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` (`lemonade/transcription.rs`) — simple, no GPU
  lock. Standalone use or NPU FLM whisper.
- `LemonadeSttProvider` (`lemonade/stt.rs`) — GPU-managed, shares
  `GpuResourceManager` with the chat provider. Use when STT may contend with
  LLM on the same GPU.

Both implement the trait. Do NOT bypass it.

### The hardware abstraction layer is gone

**There is no `DeviceWorker` trait and no `hardware/` module.** Removed in the
hardware refactor. Physical device differences are handled by `ModelSelector`
(picks the right recipe/backend per device slot) and `ProviderFactory`
(constructs the appropriate provider type). See `lemonade/selector.rs` and
`lemonade/provider_factory.rs`.

### New AI capability wiring

The end-to-end path for embedding, transcription, TTS, LLM generation, or
reranking is always:

1. `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover(url)` — fetches `/models`, `/system-info`,
   `/health` concurrently.
2. `ModelSelector::new(catalog, config)` — picks best downloaded model per
   capability + device slot; deduplicates to one provider per slot.
3. `ProviderFactory::build(sel, capability, url, queue_depth, gpu_mgr, already_loaded)`.
   Pass `catalog.loaded` IDs as `already_loaded` to skip `/load` round-trips
   for models already in RAM.
4. `InferenceQueueBuilder::with_provider(built_provider)` to register.

`AppView::do_init_lemonade()` is the canonical example: fetch → select → build
providers → degrade gracefully on any failure.

### `KnowledgeGraph` has no AI dependency

No `InferenceQueue`, no embedding field, no Lemonade dependency. Storage and
schema operations are fully synchronous and work with zero running services.
AI capabilities are opt-in — construct them separately. **Do not regress this.**

### GPU manager attachment is automatic

`LemonadeChatProvider` holds an `Option<Arc<GpuResourceManager>>`.
`ProviderFactory` attaches the manager for llamacpp:rocm/vulkan/metal recipes
and omits it for FLM (NPU) and kokoro (CPU). Do not set this field manually.

